How This Investment Works. As the winning bidder, you will collect 100% of payments until you receive the fixed amount of $432,000 from this asset. 

Early Repayment. The seller of this asset can repay the remaining advance balance at any time.For example: If after two years, this asset has paid you $285,000 and the seller wants the royalty stream back, they can pay you $147,000 to reclaim the royalties.

This catalog cannot be added to the Secondary Market of The Exchange. 

Earnings Note: "Under The Influence" saw a surge in popularity following viral attention on TikTok in 2022, prompting its official release as a single. The spike in earnings for Q3 and Q4 of 2023 reflects the impact of the song's re-release. The song also qualified for ASCAP's Audio Feature Premium. $151,607 of the last 12 months earnings were the result of this bonus. Excluding this bonus, the last 12 months earnings are $191,675. These are not expected to recur in the future but should any song in the catalog qualify again, the winning buyer will receive that bonus.
performing_artist_analysis:
"Under The Influence," originally part of Chris Brown's Indigo album's extended version, was first released on October 4, 2019. Following a surprising surge in popularity on social media, particularly TikTok, the track was officially released as a single on September 6, 2022. After its re-release, the song reached the Top 40 on the Billboard Hot 100, achieved a Platinum certification from the RIAA, and, with 1.4 billion streams, now stands as Chris Brown's most-streamed track on Spotify. This renewed attention showcases its cultural relevance and demonstrates the power of social media to amplify songs well after their initial release. 

"Lower Body" is a collaboration between Chris Brown and Nigerian artist Davido. It was also released as part of the deluxe edition of Brown's 2019 Indigo album. This track merged Brown’s R&B sound with Afrobeat influences, showing his versatility and his interest in global music trends. "Lower Body" marked another step in Chris Brown’s engagement with international sounds, appealing to both American and African audiences.
title: Chris Brown’s “Under The Influence" + “Lower Body” - Songwriter Royalties
